Is it possible to populate a NestedList from XML data?

This works fine:

var store = new Ext.data.TreeStore({
    model: 'ListItem',
    proxy: {
        type: 'ajax',
        url: '/albums/catalogue.json',
        reader: {
            type: 'tree',
            root: 'items'
        }
    }
});

But if I switch it so that it fetches an XML representation of the catalogue, like this:

    url: '/albums/catalogue.xml'

It doesn't work, and raises an error in the console:

    Uncaught Ext.data.JsonReader.getResponseData: Unable to parse JSON returned by Server.

Normally, when you fetch JSON, the reader should be set to `type: 'json'`, but in the working example above, it is set to `type: 'tree'` instead. I can't find any mention of a tree reader in the API.



I wanted to test whether it was possible to load XML data for the NestedList. 

NestedListDemo.store = new Ext.data.TreeStore({
    model: 'ListItem',
    root: NestedListDemo.data,
    proxy: {
        type: 'ajax',
        url: '/albums/catalogue.xml',
        reader: {
            type: 'xml',
            root: 'items',
            record: 'item'
        }
    }
});
